The Middle Class Task Force is holding a meeting in St. Louis, Missouri, to discuss ways to make college more affordable for families. Vice President Biden emphasizes the importance of education in improving the standard of living for the middle class. The task force aims to ensure that public policy helps middle-class families achieve their aspirations, particularly in providing affordable college education. The Obama Administration has invested in Pell grants, Federal Work Study, and revamped the Perkins loan program to make college more accessible. The administration also plans to study ways to improve the effectiveness and reliability of 529 savings plans for college. The Middle Class Task Force released a staff report highlighting the challenges of paying for college and proposing policy steps to make college more affordable for all families.